<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,592,1004]" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">
<tableCitation box="[198,285,592,618]" captionStart="TABLE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,231,1055,1076]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 3. Number of Macroclinium species by country." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF0C6606095B587AFF1842535E8CFBDB" pageId="5" pageNumber="17" tableUuid="DF0C6606095B587AFF1842535E8CFBDB">Table 3</tableCitation>
presents the diversity of the genus by country as well as the species that are endemic to each. The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barbosa-Rodrigues" authorityYear="1882" box="[229,398,631,656]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Macroclinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[229,398,631,656]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">Macroclinium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is most diverse along a relatively narrow strip of tropical cloud forests ranging from central 
<collectingCountry box="[242,375,669,695]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
into 
<collectingCountry box="[440,535,669,695]" name="Panama" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">Panama</collectingCountry>
southward into the northwestern Andes of 
<collectingCountry box="[1068,1190,669,695]" name="Colombia" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[1204,1307,669,695]" name="Ecuador" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1373,1431,669,695]" name="Peru" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">Peru</collectingCountry>
, where most of the species occur. There is a secondary centre of diversity in the western Amazonian region with 12 species. However, with the exception of 3-4 species, these are all restricted to the low-lying Amazonian slopes of the Andes, where there is a continuum of narrowly distributed species, discontinuously arranged along an elevational gradient. Thus, there are apparently no sharp limits between the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barbosa-Rodrigues" authorityYear="1882" box="[1270,1435,824,849]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Macroclinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1270,1435,824,849]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">Macroclinium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
biotas of the two biogeographical areas. There are only a few species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Barbosa-Rodrigues" authorityYear="1882" box="[1030,1198,863,888]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Macroclinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1030,1198,863,888]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">Macroclinium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as we go eastward, away from the Andes, and these are widely distributed, e.g. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dodson" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Schweinfurth" baseAuthorityYear="1946" box="[860,999,902,927]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Macroclinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mirabile">
<emphasis box="[860,999,902,927]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">M. mirabile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dodson" authorityYear="1984" baseAuthorityName="Focke" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[1057,1332,902,927]" class="Liliopsida" family="Orchidaceae" genus="Macroclinium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="5" pageNumber="17" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="wullschlaegelianum">
<emphasis box="[1057,1332,902,927]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">M. wullschlaegelianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ranging into the Guayana region. Absence of the genus is noteworthy in central and southestern 
<collectingCountry box="[1209,1285,940,966]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="17">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, and there is low diversity in the Guayana region and Megamexico. The genus is totally absent from the West Indies.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-Table-UUID="DF0C6606095B587AFF1842535E8CFBDB" box="[151,695,1055,1077]" httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF0C6606095B587AFF1842535E8CFBDB" pageId="5" pageNumber="17" startId="5.[151,231,1055,1076]" targetBox="[165,1291,1109,1811]" targetIsTable="true" targetPageId="5">
